id":"FA3F2F1925E04AF4A54AC62FB19B4C86","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Bring the salt mixture to a slow boil. Add 50 grams of disodium salt of EDTA to the boiling mixture, acid form (Na<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2 <\/span><span>EDTA.2H<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2<\/span><span>O; molecular weight is 372.24; final concentration in the 1L solution is 134 mM). <\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":952628,"guid":"0F9B2FD0A39311EAAD50771B85442C41","previous_id":952627,"previous_guid":"074F02C0A39311EAAD50771B85442C41","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"761BD0B30317445BB4E2CAAD47124183","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Preparation of Hutner's trace element"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"47A21D44D1094A74A47B36DE2C466CF0","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Add KOH pellets <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">(and not NaOH)<\/span><span> to the boiling mixture to adjust the pH to 6.5. Make up the volume to 1L with pure water after adjusting the pH to 6.5.The solution should be clear green at this point. <\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":952629,"guid":"64676880A39311EAAD50771B85442C41","previous_id":952628,"previous_guid":"0F9B2FD0A39311EAAD50771B85442C41","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"DEB32BA9B8C24855823CE64AC29E3374","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Preparation of Hutner's trace element"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"4F953B07EB3F420486F86EE84040CA7D","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Pour the green solution in a 1 L bottle. Close the cap not too tightly. Shake it occasionally every week. The color will slowly change to dark magenta\/purplish color over time. If you see any brown precipitate, filter the solution through two layers of Whatman#1 filter paper, repeating the filtration if necessary until the solution is clear.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":952630,"guid":"93D3E940A39311EAAD50771B85442C41","previous_id":952629,"previous_guid":"64676880A39311EAAD50771B85442C41","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"12A002CE5D8E46F6955FB202C13D35B1","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Preparation of  TAP medium"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"831775F3CC714CFD9C004AE62F6C4930","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">To make the final TAP medium, mix the following in 950 L of water:<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">2.42 g Tris base\/Trizma , 25 ml solution #1 (salts), 0.375 ml solution #2 (phosphate), 1.0 ml solution #3 (trace elements) and 1.0 ml glacial acetic acid (0.1% in the final 1 L of TAP medium). <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":952632,"guid":"C7885770A39411EAAD50771B85442C41","previous_id":953089,"previous_guid":"06B6E690A44511EA80C865E0BC888EF0","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"DBACD5541C08481BA313751C1F1FD550","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Preparation of TAP-agar plates"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"1274DCDD9E1748DD991C9B96CBD8077D","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>For preparing solid TAP-agar media plates to maintain <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Chlamydomonas<\/span><span> in lab, add 15 grams of agar per liter of the media after checking the pH, shake it and then autoclave. <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Note:<\/span><span> Make sure to have a magnetic stir bar inside the agar media bottle before you autoclave the bottle. Stirring using a magnetic stirrer is required during the cooling of the hot media after autoclaving to mix agar uniformly in the media solution before pouring media plates.<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#EA9F6C","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":952633,"guid":"D0D9E690A39411EAAD50771B85442C41","previous_id":952632,"previous_guid":"C7885770A39411EAAD50771B85442C41","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"824168AE85C8416AA939C2465E9DADA8","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Preparation of TP medium"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"59FF0A9ED4A24B76BEC0715554377E1B","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">TP medium is prepared exactly the same way as the TAP medium, except glacial acetic acid is not added. Hence TP medium has no carbon souce. Nothing will grow on it unless you add a carbon source to the TP medium. You will pH the TP medium like you would for making TAP medium. You can add your preferred alternative carbon source (e.g. glucose, sucrose, lactose, hydrocarbons, aromatic compounds and polyhydroxyalkanoates etc.) for testing biochemical abilites of bacteria to use exogenous carbon sources for energy production and growth.  <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_col